The paper deals with geometric graph theory and algorithms, specifically the visibility graph of a set of points and non-crossing line segments in the plane. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses spanners, which are a topic in graph theory (cs.DM) and graph algorithms (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the construction of a plane graph with bounded degree, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.DM) and graph drawing (cs.GR).
